category: SHAKESPEARE REWRITES THE BEATLES
category comment: (Ken: You'll have to name the song that the Bard has reworked in each case.)

clue: "The lady is enamored of thee, verily, verily, verily"

response: "She Loves You"

clue: "Wilt thou still require me, wilt thou still provide sustenance unto me, roughly midway through my 7th decade?"

response: "When I'm Sixty-Four"

clue: "Aid me if thou canst, I feel sorrow... & my gratitude is large for thy presence here"

response: "Help!"

clue: "Dear gentleman or lady, wouldst thou peruse my volume? It hath taken me long to pen, wouldst thou peer at it?"

response: "Paperback Writer"

clue: "I believe I shall be melancholy, I believe it shall be anon... the woman who disturbeth my temper is leaving hence"

response: "Ticket To Ride"

